reviews.text: The worst k-food restaurant that I tried in HK. All foods that I ordered, including small dishes, are below standard and the price is not reasonable.

I love this place!!!!!! Will definitely recommend to anyone that is a fan of Korean food/good food in general. Price is low, portions are good, atmosphere is how it should be at a korean restaurant and the staff are very nice. Will be coming back very soon

Small neighborhood  Korean restaurant serving traditional food. Fast service, no views. Decor is very basic. Food is quite tasty. the pricing is moderate for Korean food. OK to try again. They will ask you the level of spiciness you would like. I ordered a pork bulogi with rice, thick came with some side dishes and a radish soup. This was accompanied  with some side dishes, kikuchi and a radish soup.

The appetizers are tasty unless the fried egg is too salty. I have ordered the barbecue set for 3~4, which included beef and pork. Beef is tender and tasty with a little bit of fat. Rice and Kimbap are served in large portion. It is better to order less food if you are not really hungry.
